    "nypl_url": "https://digitalcollections.nypl.org/items/8dad0ac0-c53c-012f-ec40-58d385a7bc34",
    "original_title": "Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 65th Street",
    "text": "Fifth Avenue, at the N.E. corner of East 65th Street, showing at that location the Temple Emanu-El, erected here in 1927 on the former site of the John Jacob Astor mansion. The photographer is viewing same from the 65th Street lateral high-way thru Central Park.\n\nThis organization was formerly located at the N.E. corner of Fifth Avenue and East 43rd Street in a synagogue erected in 1868. Their earlier meetings were held in the Grand Street Court-room (1845 to 1850). Subsequently they purchased a former church on Chrystie Street and remodelled same for their purpose (1850 to 1856). A Baptist church building on East 12th Street preceded the first - Fifth Avenue structure (1856 to 1868).\n\nView 1: May 21, 1933\nView 2: April 23, 1938\n\nP. L. Sperr\n",
    "text_source": "gpt",
